<h1 id="about-gemix">About Gemix</h1>
<p>In the slot Gemix you’re playing on a 7x7 grid with cascading symbols.  As the symbols fall down they’re forming winning combinations which are removed.  Winning requires at least three adjacent symbols either vertically and/or horizontally. After a winning combination the game removes the winning symbols with new symbols falling down, replacing them. New winning combinations appearing after the first win has a multiplier applied to them. Because of this symbols keep on falling as long as there are winning combinations on the reels.</p>
<h2 id="game-features">Game Features</h2>
<p>Gemix is a unique game in many ways. This is not only due to the grid but it also has three different worlds. These worlds are called Miners World, Princess’ World and Wizards World. That however isn’t all, Gemix also has a Crystal Charge meter which activates certain functions.</p>
<h3 id="game-worlds">Game Worlds</h3>
<p>Starting the game or reaching a new world activates a pattern on the grid. Whenever a winning combination is covering a part of the pattern that part is considered hit. Hitting all parts of the pattern activates the next pattern. After completing three patterns the game sends you to the next world, receiving the entire accumulated World Bonus.</p>
<h4 id="miners-world---falling-wilds">Miners World - Falling Wilds</h4>
<p>The Miner’s lamp symbol is exclusive to the Miner’s World. Wild symbols falls from above replacing any symbols they land in front of. As few as three and as many as ten symbols are landing this way. The game will be removing these wilds as usual when they are part of a winning combination.</p>
<h4 id="princess-world---spreading-wild">Princess’ World - Spreading Wild</h4>
<p>This worlds unique symbol is the Princess’ lollipop that’s used for activating Spreading Wilds. One of the Edge symbols is selected transforming it into a wild symbol. Since this is a Spreading Wild the game selects one adjacent (diagonally, vertically or horizontally) symbol randomly transforming that into a wild as well. This procedure will be repeating itself until it reaches one of the edge symbols on the grid (not excluding the starting point). Winning combinations are causing both wilds and normal symbols to disappear as usual.</p>
